: December–February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="542" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,404,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="542">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named after the prominent Norwegian entomologist, Leif Aarvik, specialist in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,277,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tortricidae</taxonomicName>
, who has also collected the specimens of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
